        <num>4-6-51</num>
        <content>
          <p>Each sales establishment shall make adequate provision to isolate, insofar as practicable, the auctioneer, weigher, clerk, and any other employee who has any duty in regard to making any record of the sale. No person shall be permitted to converse with any such employee while the employee is performing any duty in connection with the sale.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1956, p. 501, ยง 6; Ga. L. 1983, p. 1161, ยง 1.)</p>
